Unofficial Translation by Insurance Regulator of Cambodia (IRC)

**Chapter 3**
**Conditions and Procedures**
**for Issuance and Renewal of Insurance Business License and Certificate**

**Section 1**
**The Issuance and Renewal of Insurance Business License**

**Article 5 ..**

Any person who aims to conduct insurance business as a company or branch of a foreign company shall apply for insurance business license to the **IRC** following the basic conditions as below:
- be a permitted entity;
- be in the form of Public Limited Company;
- have at least 2 (two) shareholders as natural persons;
- have minimum capital in Riel equivalent to 5,000,000 (five million) SDR as per prevailing rate at the issuance of the license;
- have a business guarantee deposit in equivalent to 10 (ten) percent of the minimum capital;
- have professional skill in insurance.

**Article 6 ..**

As the first step, before applying for a license, a person shall apply for principle approval for conducting business as a general insurance company or life insurance company or foreign insurance company branch by attaching the required documents as below:
- the application for principle approval for conducting business as a general insurance company or life insurance company or foreign insurance company branch;
- the receipt of administrative fee;
- the document of feasibility study on the Cambodian insurance market;
- the 5 (five) -years business plan;
- the draft statute of the company that will be established;
- A copy of shareholder's identification:
    • for shareholder as a natural person shall provide a passport or ID Card
    • for shareholder as a legal entity shall provide legal business document and head office address;
- A copy of the identification and qualifications of the person to be appointed as chairman of the board of director and director, including a passport or ID card, a resume on work experience and study attached with a degree or professional certificate;
- the proof of reserved company name at the Ministry of Commerce;
- In the case of a subsidiary or foreign insurance company branch, the additional documents shall be provided as below:
    • A copy and certified by the notary of approval letter or business license of the parent company or the principal issued by the competent authority of the country of origin, in case the parent company or the principal is an insurance company;
    • A copy and certified by the notary of decision of the board of directors of the parent company or the principal authorizing to conduct the insurance business in the Kingdom of Cambodia;

